Written evidence from the National Council for Voluntary Organisations (NCVO) [PUB00012] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]About NCVO [bold]NCVO champions and strengthens the voluntary sector, with over 10,000 members, from the largest charities to the smallest community organisations. Alongside our sister councils in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland, we make sure the voluntary sector can do what it does best 
[normal]www.ncvo.org.uk
[normal]. 
[normal]NCVO convenes the Public Service Delivery Network, a group of 2500 organisations that have an interest in public service delivery. NCVO also convenes a Special Interest Group (SIG) of sub-contractor organisations involved in the Work Programme, and a Payment-by-Results working group that will be making recommendations in late 2013.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Summary [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Government’s policy goals, as expressed in the Open Public Services white paper, are positive and could support more effective and open public services. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]However, at present, poor commissioning and procurement practice is hampering the Government’s ambitions. Ultimately, this will impact on the quality of public services. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Public bodies are focussing on securing the cheapest price, rather than assessing value for money. This can exclude voluntary organisations and SMEs from public service delivery. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Other barriers facing voluntary organisations include: inappropriate procurement approaches; larger contract sizes; short procurement timescales and disproportionate bidding requirements. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Many VCSEs are unable to participate in payment-by-results (
[normal]PbR
[normal]) contracts because of the cash flow and working capital requirements to the detriment of market diversity and user experience. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]There is a lack of open and consistent data available, despite its importance for effective policy formation, driving improvements in procurement and securing better value for public money. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Improving commissioning and procurement requires focussing on culture as much as procedure. Increased training and support for commissioners and procurement professionals will be vital if the government’s objectives to deliver better public services are to be achieved. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Citizen-led delivery of public services relies on the trust and commitment of local communities, these communities are often mobilised around particular voluntary or community groups; if properly supported these groups can provide a route for more effective services. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Introduction - the voluntary sector’s role in public service delivery [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q1. To what extent is the Government’s public service reform programme succeeding in: b. [bold]Improving[bold] public services? c. Ensuring that public services are accountable to the people who use them, and to elected officials? [bold]&#xa0;
