[normal]Q6. How well do different tiers of government or different parts of single public sector organisation, at central, local authority or district [bold]councils[bold] level, work together to deliver public services? [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]________________________
[normal]31[bold] Furthermore, 49% of Blue Sky’s employees have gone on to further employment. More examples of VCSEs delivering social value: 
[normal]http://www.ncvo-vol.org.uk/policy-research/public-services/what-we-believe. 
[normal]32[bold] 
[normal]http://www.ncvo.org.uk/images/documents/policy_and_research/campaigning/sme_consultation_response.pdf 
[normal]33[bold] Essex County Council has already achieved a 60% success rate for high risk victims of domestic abuse that previously declined to engage with Essex police prior to service transformation. Greater Manchester is looking to reduce the number of people on out of work benefits by 22%, delivering annual savings of £500 million. 
