[normal]35[bold] Over one-third (137) of all local authorities in England and Wales have applied for the programme, highlighting the public sector’s appetite for innovation when support exists to help achieve this: 
[normal]http://www.nesta.org.uk/areas_of_work/public_services_lab/local_public_services/creative_councils
[normal]. 
[normal]36[bold] Barnet Council have been working with VCSE organisation My Society, to develop Barnet Pledgebank36designed to assist residents in organizing their own projects, from tackling graffiti to setting up computer classes in their area. 
[normal]37[bold] For a step by step guide to harnessing best practice and innovation from the voluntary sector throughout the commissioning process see 
